Target of this Project ¶

In this project,I will analyze San Francisco where I live temperature data and global temperature and compare the temperature trends of them.

Extract the data ¶

  • Write a SQL query to extract the city level data. Export to CSV. 
    SELECT *
FROM city_data
WHERE city = 'San Francisco'
;
  • Write a SQL query to extract the global data. Export to CSV. 
    SELECT *
FROM global_data
;

Temperature data analysis¶

Use python data analyze model "pandas" to analysis and loading csv file.

From data set global average temperature data start at 1750 and end of 2015,most of average temperature not over 10 degrees celsius.From my live city of San Francisco temperature data set start at 1849 and end of 2013.most of average temperature between 14 - 16 degree celsius.

Plots¶

In [11]:
plt.figure(figsize=(20,8))
plt.plot(global_data.year, global_data.avg_temp,label='Global_avg_temp')
plt.axhline(global_data.avg_temp.mean(), color='k', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2,label='Global_avg_temp_mean')
plt.legend()
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Temperature(℃)')
plt.title('Global Weather Trends')
plt.xticks(np.arange(1750, 2016, step=5), rotation=40)
plt.show()

From global average temperature trends fold line,as we can see the global temperature on the up trend.

Moving average and plots ¶

Setting temperature moving average of 5 years,7years and 10 years then saving into "global_data" and "sf_data"

In [27]:
n = 5
global_data['moving_avg5'] = global_data['avg_temp'].rolling(window=n).mean()
sf_data['moving_avg5'] = sf_data['avg_temp'].rolling(window=n).mean()

n = 7
global_data['moving_avg7'] = global_data['avg_temp'].rolling(window=n).mean()
sf_data['moving_avg7'] = sf_data['avg_temp'].rolling(window=n).mean()

n = 10
global_data['moving_avg10'] = global_data['avg_temp'].rolling(window=n).mean()
sf_data['moving_avg10'] = sf_data['avg_temp'].rolling(window=n).mean()

Analysis and Summary¶

1. Is your city hotter or cooler on average compared to the global average? Has the difference been consistent over time?¶

San Francisco has a warm-summer Mediterranean climate (Köppen Csb) characteristic of California's coast, with moist mild winters and dry summers.Because of its sharp topography and maritime influences, San Francisco exhibits a multitude of distinct microclimates.San Francisco temperaure hotter than global average and compared to global average the difference been consistent same as over time approximate 7 degree celsius.

2.“How do the changes in your city’s temperatures over time compare to the changes in the global average?”¶

Overall,San Francisco and global average are instability changed before 1900.And start from 1900,San Francisco and global temperaures are steadily growth.there have peak average in recent year as San Francisco: 16.23 degree clesius and gobal:9.83 degree clesius.

3.What does the overall trend look like? Is the world getting hotter or cooler? Has the trend been consistent over the last few hundred years?¶

To observation the whole weather trends the world is getting hotter and San Francisco as well,experically in last few hundred years.from san francisco 10 years moving average plot is clearly to shows start from 1925 the temperature has highly rising up after that year the temperature has come down,from 1955 the temperature has steadily growth the peak temperature is 15.14 clesius.the gobal temperature steadily growth from 1975 the peak 10 years moving average temperature is 9.59 clesius.

In conclusion,from the fold lines have same up-trend that can be predict global and San francisco temperature will continue to raising up.Is that will effect on global ecosystem or human living actuality? That will have more research to determine it.
